    <main class="container">
        <section id="biography">
            <h2>Biography</h2>
            <div class="bio-content">
                <p>Nelson Rolihlahla Mandela was born on July 18, 1918, in the village of Mvezo in South Africa. He became one of the most revered figures in modern history, dedicating his life to the fight against apartheid and the pursuit of equality, justice, and human dignity for all people.</p>
                
                <p>Mandela's journey from a rural village to becoming South Africa's first Black president is a testament to his unwavering commitment to justice. He studied law at the University of Fort Hare and the University of the Witwatersrand, where he became involved in anti-colonial politics and joined the African National Congress (ANC) in 1944.</p>
                
                <p>For his activism against the apartheid government, Mandela was imprisoned for 27 years, from 1962 to 1990. Rather than breaking his spirit, this experience strengthened his resolve and made him a global symbol of resistance to oppression. His release from prison marked the beginning of South Africa's transition to democracy.</p>
                
                <p>In 1994, Mandela was elected as South Africa's first Black president in the country's first fully representative democratic election. His presidency was marked by efforts to dismantle the legacy of apartheid through reconciliation and the establishment of a "Rainbow Nation" where all races could coexist peacefully.</p>
                
                <p>Mandela's legacy extends far beyond South Africa. He became a global icon of peace, reconciliation, and human rights, inspiring movements for justice around the world. His philosophy of forgiveness over revenge helped heal a nation and showed the world the power of reconciliation.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="quote-section">
            <div class="quote">"Education is the most powerful weapon which you can use to change the world."</div>
            <div class="quote-author">- Nelson Mandela</div>
        </section>

        <section id="achievements">
            <h2>Major Achievements</h2>
            <div class="achievements-grid">
                <div class="achievement">
                    <div class="achievement-year">1944</div>
                    <h3>Joined the ANC</h3>
                    <p>Became a member of the African National Congress and co-founded the ANC Youth League, beginning his lifelong fight against apartheid.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="achievement">
                    <div class="achievement-year">1952</div>
                    <h3>Defiance Campaign</h3>
                    <p>Led the Defiance Campaign against unjust laws, establishing himself as a prominent anti-apartheid activist.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="achievement">
                    <div class="achievement-year">1964</div>
                    <h3>Rivonia Trial Speech</h3>
                    <p>Delivered his famous "I am prepared to die" speech, becoming a symbol of resistance to oppression worldwide.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="achievement">
                    <div class="achievement-year">1990</div>
                    <h3>Release from Prison</h3>
                    <p>Released after 27 years in prison, immediately resuming his role as a leader in the fight for democracy.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="achievement">
                    <div class="achievement-year">1993</div>
                    <h3>Nobel Peace Prize</h3>
                    <p>Awarded the Nobel Peace Prize jointly with F.W. de Klerk for their work in ending apartheid peacefully.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="achievement">
                    <div class="achievement-year">1994</div>
                    <h3>First Black President</h3>
                    <p>Elected as South Africa's first Black president, leading the country's transition to democracy.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

