        <section id="legacy">
            <h2>Legacy</h2>
            <div class="bio-content">
                <p>Nelson Mandela's legacy transcends borders and generations. His unwavering commitment to justice, equality, and human dignity transformed not only South Africa but inspired liberation movements and human rights advocates worldwide. His philosophy of reconciliation over revenge showed the world that even the deepest wounds can heal through forgiveness and understanding.</p>
                
                <p>The Nelson Mandela Foundation continues his work in promoting social justice and human rights. Mandela Day, celebrated annually on July 18th, encourages people worldwide to dedicate 67 minutes of their time to helping others – representing the 67 years Mandela devoted to public service.</p>
                
                <p>His autobiography, "Long Walk to Freedom," remains one of the most influential memoirs of the 20th century. His speeches and writings continue to inspire leaders, activists, and ordinary citizens who seek to create a more just and equitable world.</p>
                
                <p>Perhaps Mandela's greatest legacy is the proof that change is possible – that systems of oppression can be dismantled through courage, persistence, and moral leadership. His life demonstrates that one person, armed with conviction and compassion, can indeed change the world. As he once said, "It always seems impossible until it's done."</p>
            </div>
        </section>
